Michelle Robin Kapp, the daughter of Dr. Minna Kapp and Fred Kapp of Bayside, Queens, was married last evening to Joseph Wayne Lorge, a son of Roslyn and Richard D. Lorge of Oceanside, N.Y. Rabbi Herbert Silverberg officiated at the Seven Hills Inn in Lenox, Mass.

Mrs. Lorge, 26, is a registered nurse in Queens for the Visiting Nurse Service of New York. She graduated from the State University of New York at Binghamton. She received a master's degree in nursing from the C. W. Post campus of Long Island University, where her mother is the chairwoman of the nursing department. The bride's father is a special-education teacher at Martin Van Buren High School in Queens Village.

Mr. Lorge, 31, is a guidance counselor at Herbert H. Lehman High School in the Bronx. He graduated from the University of Maryland and received a master's degree in school counseling from C. W. Post. His mother teaches first grade at the Florence A. Smith Elementary School in Oceanside, N.Y.; she is also the vice president of the Oceanside Federation of Teachers. His father, a lawyer, has a private practice in Westbury, N.Y.